Totally fair. When you're at the server, all you need to do is:

1. Copy the current `config/site.css` to `config/site-full.css` (replacing the stub that's there now)
2. Replace `config/site.css` with just:

```css
/* SeedPods codex overrides — layered on top of the Gossamer default CSS */

/* Pod header: tighten bottom padding below the prev/next nav row */
.pod-header{padding:1.5rem 0 1rem}
```

Then build and see what the default CSS gives you. Anything that looks wrong, we add back as an override.

Sorry for the runaround — the edit system really isn't built for replacing an entire large file. Good thing to know for next time.

